content:
Load Cached Visualforce Site Pages Faster

To improve page load times, the caching behavior is updated for public site pages built in Visualforce. When an unauthenticated user visits a login-enabled site and the Visualforce page is cached, the cached version exists on the proxy server and the end userâ€™s web browser. Previously, the page was cached only on the proxy server.

Where: This change applies to Visualforce sites and Salesforce Sites accessed through Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.
title: Improving Visualforce Page Load Times
